<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 An explosion and fire ripped through a building today, injuring at least two bomb-squad officers investigating a fireworks blast that tore off part of a youth's hand hours earlier, authorities said. Officers with burns and facial cuts were taken to two hospitals, where their conditions were not available, said Firefighter <PERSON> Jim </PERSON> <PERSON> Williamson </PERSON>. `` It's too confusing right now to tell just how many were injured,'' he said. `` It's anywhere from two to seven, and we think they're all officers.'' About 35 firefighters put out the blaze at a Victorian structure described as either a single-family house or small apartment building, he said. The youth injured by fireworks was treated at <ORGANIZATION> Cedars-Sinai </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Medical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION>, police said. The victim's condition was not available.
