<HEAD>Two Jets Collide on Ground at Heathrow, No Injuries</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: LEADS throughout to UPDATE with aviation official's comment;
no pickup</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The wing of a taxiing jetliner clipped the tail section of another today at <LOCATION> Heathrow </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Airport </LOCATION> as the aircraft were preparing to take off, but none of the 480 people on the planes was injured, airline officials said. The incident involved a <ORGANIZATION> British </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airways </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Boeing </ORGANIZATION> 757 carrying 111 passengers and seven crew members to <LOCATION> Brussels </LOCATION> and a <ORGANIZATION> Thai </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airways </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Boeing </ORGANIZATION> 747 en route to <LOCATION> Bangkok </LOCATION>. Both jets suffered minor damage when the wing of the Thai jet struck the tail section of the stationary <ORGANIZATION> British </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airways </ORGANIZATION> jet as the <LOCATION> Bangkok </LOCATION> flight was taxiing toward the runway, said <PERSON> Linda </PERSON> <PERSON> Jones </PERSON>, a spokeswoman for <ORGANIZATION> British </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airways </ORGANIZATION>. `` It was actually a very minor accident,'' Ms. <PERSON> Jones </PERSON> said. `` People on board probably were not aware of it.'' <ORGANIZATION> British </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airways </ORGANIZATION> passengers were transferred to another plane. Thai Airways was making alternative arrangements for its 348 passengers, said airline spokesman <PERSON> Jeff </PERSON> <PERSON> Bacall </PERSON>. The Thai flight had a 21-member crew. A <ORGANIZATION> Civil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Aviation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Authority </ORGANIZATION> spokeswoman, speaking on condition of anonymity in keeping with British practice, said: `` It is a reportable incident and will be investigated by the Air Investigations Branch.''
