<TEXT>
 The full-figured look just did n't suit a woman who arrived on a flight from <LOCATION> Guatemala </LOCATION>, and federal agents found she was wearing four girdles stuffed with cocaine. <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Customs </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> agents detained the 38-year-old Colombian woman Monday while she stood in line for a baggage search at <LOCATION> Houston </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Intercontinental </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Airport </LOCATION>. `` An agent noticed she was very nervous and that she was wearing very bulky clothing,'' said <PERSON> Candace </PERSON> <PERSON> Vice </PERSON>, chief customs inspector at the airport. `` We continued the inspection and discovered 16.3 pounds of cocaine secreted inside four girdles she was wearing,'' Ms. <PERSON> Vice </PERSON> said. She said the woman was holding a ticket for a flight from <LOCATION> Houston </LOCATION> to <LOCATION> Amsterdam </LOCATION>. `` She was apparently heading to <LOCATION> Holland </LOCATION> because the value of cocaine is much greater there,'' she said. The cocaine would have been worth about three times more than the estimated $ 92,000 it would fetch in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, she said.
