o appeal. The ruling orders <ORGANIZATION> HUD </ORGANIZATION> and the state to require owners of all government-assisted housing in metropolitan <LOCATION> Boston </LOCATION> to participate fully in anti-discrimination programs. It also orders <LOCATION> Boston </LOCATION> to create a clearinghouse with a list of federally assisted housing units. In 1985, <PERSON> Skinner </PERSON> dismissed the lawsuit, saying he lacked authority to review and correct <ORGANIZATION> HUD </ORGANIZATION> practices. In 1987, an appeals court said <PERSON> Skinner </PERSON> did have authority and ordered him to reopen the case.
