<HEAD>Official Says Jailed Financier Will Fight Extradition</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BERN, Switzerland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Saudi financier <PERSON> Adnan </PERSON> <PERSON> Khashoggi </PERSON> says he will fight extradition to the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, where he is accused of helping <PERSON> Ferdinand </PERSON> and <PERSON> Imelda </PERSON> <PERSON> Marcos </PERSON> hide stolen wealth, a Swiss official reported Tuesday. <PERSON> Marcos </PERSON> and his wife are accused in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> of stealing more than $ 100 million in Philippine government money to buy real estate and art objects before he was ousted as president in February 1986. <PERSON> Khashoggi </PERSON> allegedly posed as the owner of some assets. <ORGANIZATION> Justice </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ministry </ORGANIZATION> spokeswoman <PERSON> Ursula </PERSON> <PERSON> Riedel </PERSON> said <PERSON> Khashoggi </PERSON> was asked, after a <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> request arrived May 31, whether he would agree to extradition. He refused and his attorneys are expected to provide an formal explanation by next week, after which Swiss authorities will rule on the extradition request, she told The <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION>. No decision is expected until mid-July and <PERSON> Khashoggi </PERSON>'s lawyers have said they will appeal any ruling against him to the <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Tribunal </ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION> Switzerland </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Supreme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Khashoggi </PERSON>, known for his middleman role in the Iran-Contra affair, was arrested by Swiss police in April at the request of the <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Embassy </ORGANIZATION>. It appears almost certain he will spend his 54th birthday, July 25, in a <LOCATION> Bern </LOCATION> jail. A <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> district court in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> indicted <PERSON> Kh