<HEAD>Authorities Step Up Pro-Condom Campaign</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PRAGUE, Czechoslovakia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Authorities are stepping up their campaign against AIDS before the peak tourist summer months, the official <ORGANIZATION> CTK </ORGANIZATION> news agency said Tuesday. Five people have died of the disease in <LOCATION> Czechoslovakia </LOCATION> and another 145 have tested positive for it, the report said. The report, quoting data submitted to the recent World Conference on AIDS in <LOCATION> Montreal </LOCATION>, said the main task of the campaign is health education. `` That is why the windows of most of <LOCATION> Prague </LOCATION>'s drugstores will remind their customers of the advatages of condom use before vacation time,'' according to the newspaper <ORGANIZATION> Mlada </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fronta </ORGANIZATION>. Acquired immune deficiency syndrome is caused by a virus that damages the body's immune system, leaving victims susceptible to infections and cancer. It is spread most often through sexual contact, needles or syringes shared by drug abusers, infected blood or blood products, and from pregnant women to their offspring. The scientific name for the virus is human immunodeficiency virus, or HIV.
