</TEXT>
<DATELINE>RALEIGH, N.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Sick of slow service? Incensed by indifference? Does bad food leave you bummed, pal? Well, for a paltry $ 2.25, you do n't have to take it anymore. Just use a Consum-Alert sticker. The stickers can be applied on the window _ or the employee if you're that angry _ of the offending business. They are n't permanent _ they use static cling and can easily be removed and leave no sticky residue. The black and gold flourescent stickers are the idea of radio announcer <PERSON> Bill </PERSON> <PERSON> Flynn </PERSON> and ad agency owner <PERSON> Greg </PERSON> <PERSON> Fischer </PERSON>. `` I can only say there have been ample opportunities in my life in the last six months where I could have used one of these things and felt justified in doing so,'' <PERSON> Flynn </PERSON> said Tuesday. `` We live in a time where it's so easy to be treated like a number.'' `` The ultimate goal is to just be able to vent ourselves,'' <PERSON> Fischer </PERSON> said. Purchasers get six decals to an order. Black letters say: `` Consum-Alert Warning! This Business Has Been Targeted By Your Fellow Consumer For'' one of four offenses. White letters on a black background indicate the offense: `` Slow Service,'' `` Poor Service,'' `` Bad Attitude'' or `` Poor Hygiene.'' There are two Poor Service stickers and two for Bad Attitude. Instructions with the stickers claim `` the feeling of self-respect and vindication you get is exhilarating.'' The stickers should be placed, according to the instructions, in a `` high-visibility, eye-level location for your Consum-Alert. Put that sucker where everyone can see it!'' The instructions do n't encourage confrontation. The pleasure of relieving frustration should be sufficient. `` You've joined the ranks of <PERSON> Robin </PERSON> <PERSON> Hood </PERSON> and The Lone Ranger. Be proud.'' Some of the proceeds from the sale of the stickers will go to the <ORGANIZATION> Better </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Business </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bureau </ORGA