<HEAD>Man Killed When National Guardsmen Fire on Peasant Protest</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BARQUEIROS, Portugal (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 National guardsmen opened fire on villagers protesting a mining operation, fatally wounding a young man, officials reported Tuesday. A National Republican Guard spokesmen said six shots were fired after a guardsman was injured Monday by villagers throwing stones. <PERSON> Carlos </PERSON> <PERSON> Simoes </PERSON>, 20, was shot in the head and taken to a hospital in <LOCATION> Oporto </LOCATION>, 45 miles away, where he died Tuesday. More than 200 residents of this northern village fought with about 80 armed guardsmen during the protest. <LOCATION> Portugal </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> is a paramilitary police force, similar to <LOCATION> Spain </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Civil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION>, that operates mainly in rural areas. Villagers say a nearby mine, where porcelain clay is extracted, pollutes the air and water and uses machinery that violates noise restrictions. The guard spokesman, whose name was withheld in keeping with regulation, said the <ORGANIZATION> Interior </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ministry </ORGANIZATION> had ordered an investigation of the use of firearms in the confrontation. At least 12 other villagers and a guardsman were treated at hospitals for injuries siffered in the fighting. Protesters fled into nearby cafes and houses. A villager reached by telephone from <LOCATION> Lisbon </LOCATION> on Tuesday said <PERSON> Barqueiros </PERSON> was calm and `` we're in mourning.'' Witnesses said the mine was operating. In a statement issued Monday, the Mibal mining company said it would not be `` intimidated by ... threats in clear disrespect of the law and democracy.'' Residents of Barqueiros boycotted <ORGANIZATION> European </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Parliament </ORGANIZATION> elections this month as part of their protest.
