<HEAD>New Statistics Required</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MIKE ROBINSON</BYLINE>
<UNK>Associated Press Writer</UNK>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The House on Tuesday approved plans to require the government to collect and publish for five years statistics on crimes based on the race, ethic group, sexual preference or religion of the victims. `` This legislation is an opportunity to begin the counterattack against crimes based on hate,'' said Rep. <PERSON> Charles </PERSON> <PERSON> E. </PERSON> <PERSON> Schumer </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-N.Y. </LOCATION>, as the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> approved the measure 368-47 and sent it to the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION>. Supporters said the nation is being hit by a growing wave of so-called hate crimes, ranging from gang attacks on members of minority groups to cross burnings and the spray painting of swastikas and bigoted slogans. Under the bill, statistics would be collected on homicide, assault, robbery, burglary, theft, arson, vandalism, trespassing, threats and others deemed appropriate by the <ORGANIZATION> Justice </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> if they involved bias involving race, ethnicity, sexual preference or religion. The House has passed similar measures in the past but the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> has not acted. A hate crimes bill was approved by the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Judiciary </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> on March 9 and supporters are hoping for a floor vote. The <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION> publishes annual crime statistics but does not include hate crimes. Supporters have relied on unofficial reports and anecdotal information from news accounts in estimating that the problem is growing worse. Rep. <PERSON> Bill </PERSON> <PERSON> Green </PERSON>, <LOCATION> R-N.Y. </LOCATION>, said 1,281 anti-semitic incidents were reported by the Anti-Defamation League of B'Nai B'rith in 1988. He said the National Gay and <ORGANIZATION> Lesbian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Task </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> reported 7,008 incidents of anti-gay violence in 1987. `` There is also evidence of growing Klan, neo-Nazi, skinhead and other hate group activity throughout the nation,'' <PERSON> Green </PERSON> said. `` The tremendous rise in crimes against minorities is widespread and extremely serious,'' Rep. <PERSON> Nancy </PERSON> <PERSON> Pelosi </PERSON>, D-Calif., said Compiling data on such acts would help in fighting them, supporters said `` The more we know about crimes of hate the more chance we have of preventing them,'' said Rep. <PERSON> Barbara </PERSON> <PERSON> B. </PERSON> <PERSON> Kennelly </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-Conn </LOCATION>. `` <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> should send a clear signal to all people that crimes based on race, religion or sexuality will not be tolerated,'' said Rep. <PERSON> Ben </PERSON> <PERSON> Gilman </PERSON>, <LOCATION> R-N </LOCATION>
