as found stuffed in a paper bag at the singer's <LOCATION> Mississippi </LOCATION> home, and a former girlfriend said <PERSON> Lewis </PERSON> once gave her $ 80,000 in a shoe box to keep for him while he was hospitalized. <PERSON> Lewis </PERSON> nearly died from a ruptured stomach in 1981 and has since had much of his stomach removed. He still gets out from time to time for late-night drinks at his favorite bars, but is becoming more of a homebody since the birth of his new son. <PERSON> Lewis </PERSON>' first son, <PERSON> Jerry </PERSON> <PERSON> Lee </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON>, was killed in a traffic accident at age 19. Aother son, <PERSON> Steve </PERSON> <PERSON> Allen </PERSON>, drowned in a swimming pool at age 3. He also has two daughters. <PERSON> Lewis </PERSON> acknowledged that many of the lumps and bumps in his life may have been of his own doing, but he stopped short of offering any apology. `` I do n't think I overshot my runway,'' he said. `` I'm still rockin', brother ... and I did it my way.''
