 <PERSON> Henry </PERSON> <PERSON> Bloch </PERSON>, 66, a co-founder of the tax preparation company <ORGANIZATION> H </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> R </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Block </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, will step aside as president Aug. 1, becoming chairman, the company announced. That position has been vacant since <PERSON> Bloch </PERSON>'s brother and co-founder, <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Bloch </PERSON>, retired in 1982, the company said Monday. <PERSON> Henry </PERSON> <PERSON> Bloch </PERSON>'s son, <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON>, 35, will become president and chief operating officer. He joined the company in 1976 and for the last year has been executive vice president. <PERSON> Jerome </PERSON> <PERSON> B. </PERSON> <PERSON> Grossman </PERSON>, 69, who has been chief operating officer and senior executive vice president, will become vice chairman, a new position. H & amp; R Block, the nation's largest income tax preparer, was founded in 1955. Its subsidiaries include <ORGANIZATION> CompuServe </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Personnel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pool </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> America </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Path </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Management </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Industries </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc </ORGANIZATION>.
